2 SENATE BILL 492
1 licensee or the registration of a registration holder if the applicant, licensee, or registration
2 holder:
3 (11) Has violated any provision of this title;
4 6–401.
5 (a) The Board shall adopt regulations to [establish]:
6 (1) ESTABLISH standards for advertising or soliciting by licensed massage
7 therapists or registered massage practitioners;
8 (2) DEFINE SPECIFIC LANGUAGE AND CONTENT PROHIBITED UNDER
9 THIS SECTION; AND
10 (3) ESTABLISH PROCEDURES FOR REPORTING VIOLATIONS OF THIS
11 SECTION BY A LICENSED MASSAGE THERAPIST, REGISTERED MASSAGE
12 PRACTITIONER, OR MEMBER OF THE PUBLIC.
13 (b) For purposes of this section, the mailing of notices to patients to inform them
14 of times for periodic appointments is not advertising or soliciting.
15 (C) (1) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION,
16 AN ADVERTISEMENT FOR MASSAGE THERAPY SERVICES SHALL INCLUDE THE FULL
17 NAME, AS STATED ON THE LICENSE OR REGISTRATION APPLICATION SUBMITTED TO
18 THE BOARD, AND LICENSE NUMBER OR REGISTRATION NUMBER OF THE LICENSED
19 MASSAGE THERAPIST OR REGISTERED MASSAGE PRACTITIONER PROVIDING THE
20 MASSAGE THERAPY SERVICES ADVERTISED.
21 (2) AN ADVERTISEMENT FOR MASSAGE THERAPY SERVICES PLACED,
22 PUBLISHED, OR DISTRIBUTED BY A BUSINESS THAT EMPLOYS OR CONTRACTS WITH
23 MULTIPLE LICENSED MASSAGE THERAPISTS OR REGISTERED MASSAGE
24 PRACTITIONERS IS NOT REQUIRED TO INCLUDE THE NAMES AND LICENSE OR
25 REGISTRATION NUMBERS OF EACH LICENSED MASSAGE THERAPIST OR REGISTERED
26 MASSAGE PRACTITIONER EMPLOYED OR CONTRACTED WITH.
27 [(c)] (D) [A] SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, A licensed
28 massage therapist or registered massage practitioner may use a trade name in connection
29 with the practice of massage therapy provided that:
30 (1) The use of the trade name is not deceptive or misleading;
31 (2) The advertisement in which the trade name appears includes the name
32 of the licensed massage therapist or registered massage practitioner or the name of the
33 business entity providing the massage therapy services being advertised, as long as the

SENATE BILL 492 3
1 advertisement includes the name of a licensed massage therapist or registered massage
2 practitioner;
3 (3) The name of the licensed massage therapist or registered massage
4 practitioner providing massage therapy services appears on the billing invoices, stationery,
5 and any receipt given to a patient; and
6 (4) Treatment records are maintained that clearly identify the licensed
7 massage therapist or registered massage practitioner who has performed the massage
8 therapy service for the patient.
9 (E) (1) A LICENSED MASSAGE THERAPIST, REGISTERED MASSAGE
10 PRACTITIONER, OR A THIRD PARTY ACTING ON BEHALF OF A LICENSED MASSAGE
11 THERAPIST OR REGISTERED MASSAGE PRACTITIONER MAY NOT PLACE, PUBLISH, OR
12 DISTRIBUTE, OR CAUSE TO BE PLACED, PUBLISHED, OR DISTRIBUTED, AN
13 ADVERTISEMENT FOR MASSAGE THERAPY SERVICES:
14 (I) THAT STATES PROSTITUTION SERVICES, ESCORT SERVICES,
15 OR SEXUAL SERVICES ARE AVAILABLE;
16 (II) ON A WEBSITE KNOWN FOR ADVERTISING PROSTITUTION
17 SERVICES, ESCORT SERVICES, OR SEXUAL SERVICES; OR
18 (III) THAT INDICATES OR IMPLIES, THROUGH LANGUAGE OR
19 OTHER CONTENT, THAT SEXUAL ACTIVITY IS PART OF THE MASSAGE THERAPY
20 SERVICE.
21 (2) FOR AN ONLINE ADVERTISEMENT, EACH DAY ON WHICH AN
22 ADVERTISEMENT THAT VIOLATES PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION IS VISIBLE
23 TO THE PUBLIC CONSTITUTES A SEPARATE VIOLATION OF THIS SECTION.
24 (3) FAILURE TO REMOVE A PHYSICAL SIGN OR BILLBOARD PLACED IN
25 PUBLIC VIEW THAT VIOLATES PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION CONSTITUTES A
26 VIOLATION OF THIS SECTION.
27 (F) ALL ADVERTISEMENTS FOR LICENSED MASSAGE THERAPISTS OR
28 REGISTERED MASSAGE PRACTITIONERS SHALL INCLUDE THE FULL NAME AS
29 LICENSED AND LICENSE NUMBER OF THE LICENSED MASSAGE THERAPIST OR
30 REGISTERED MASSAGE PRACTITIONER PROVIDING THE ADVERTISED MASSAGE
31 THERAPY SERVICES.
32 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
33 October 1, 2026.

